The paper discusses the design and validation of an agent-based collision avoidance component for autonomous vehicles, which involves incorporating human cognition and emotions. This topic falls under the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
